<TITLE> Muggers snatch Tk 69 lakh in Narsingdi </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narshingdi, Mar 4 (bdnews24.com)  Muggers shot a spinning factory official and snatched Tk 69lakhs from him at Shibpur upazila around 3pm on Thursday. OC of Shibpur police station Majibur Rahman Majumder told bdnews24.com that Jahidul Islam, assistant managing director of Thermax Group of Companies, was on his way to a the spinning factory located at Panchkandi area of Monohardi. "He had earlier drawn money for workers salary from a bank in Narshingdi. Muggers blocked the microbus carrying him at Itkhola area around 3pm on Thursday and tried to snatch the money. They shot Jahidul as he attempted to stop them." Jahidul was taken to Shibpur upazila health centre and then to Dhaka Medical College Hospital, he said. The driver of the microbus and an accompanying official of the company were also injured in the squabble with the muggers and were released following treatment at Shibpur upazila health centre. A case is being filed regarding the incident. bdnews2
